<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When specifying a requirement for a variable in a route to be one of two values via a 'pipe', a prefix of the first value, or a postfix of the last will match too.</p>

<p>Example:
When a requirement set as 'view|edit', the values 'viewSet' and 'blablaedit' will also match.</p>

<p>Cause of problem:
The string specified is passed through {{preg_match('#^'. $requirement .'$#ui')}}.</p>

<p>Solution:
Add () around the string to be matched: {{preg_match('#^('. $requirement .')$#ui')}}.
This solution is more correct and predictable, however it will also break old code if it (ab)used this undocumented possibility to avoid the '^' &amp; '$'.</p>

    </div>
